Supabase, Auth & Security

Initial Setup Requirements

Environment Variables: Before coding, ensure .env.local contains NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY.

Schema Initialization: Since the account is new, the AI must provide a complete SQL migration script (Tables: profiles, properties, travel_applications) for the user to run in the Supabase SQL Editor before implementing data-fetching logic.

Auth Implementation

Use @supabase/ssr for session management.

Roles: Verify user roles (admin, agent, client) by querying the profiles table.

Middleware: Maintain middleware.ts to protect private route groups. Redirect users based on their role and authentication status.

Data Fetching Pattern

Use lib/supabase/server.ts for Server Component queries.

Use lib/supabase/client.ts for Client Component interactivity.

Security: Never bypass Row Level Security (RLS). Every database table must have RLS enabled.

Agent Specifics

Implementation must check for verified: true and onboarding_paid: true (the ₦5,000 fee from PRD) before allowing agents to submit listings.